The Creepypasta Layer: “The Imagowithin ‘Aliicide’ Frequency”
A key meta-element emerged in April 2026 via Reddit. User u/Plutointampa
(self-identified with the “imagowithin” ecosystem)
posted a creepypasta in r/creepypasta titled “Case Study: The Imagowithin 
‘Aliicide’ Frequency.” It fictionalizes the hunt for Ivan Munson: a man from Oxnard
whose “soul” becomes a digital codec haunting fiber-optic cables between Washington
state and Mérida. Features include glitched ads, a file called “The Aliicide Protocol”
blending breathing, dam hums, and mystical Jewish whispers, GPS glitches, and a final
message : “You spent so long looking for me in Mérida, you forgot to check if I was 
already inside the signal."
The author (Plutointampa) interacts positively with @imagowithin on X and the post itself.
Parallel posts in r/atmosphericblackmetal and r/BlackMetalCringe offer a harsher counter-narrative: Aliicide as a “digital footprint of a slow-motion car crash,” a fentanyl-fueled vanity project involving pawned instruments, emaciated selfies, and unfulfilled promises.
These read like extended roasts but mirror the project’s own self-referential “death” motifs. 




